content.text: If a variable should have a fixed value that cannot be changed, you can use the const keyword.
content.html: If a variable should have a fixed value that cannot be changed, you can use the const keyword.

content.text: The const keyword declares the variable as "constant", which means that it is unchangeable and read-only .
content.html: The const keyword declares the variable as "constant", which means that it is unchangeable and read-only.

content.code_html: const CONSTNAME type = value

content.text: Note: The value of a constant must be assigned when you declare it.
content.html: Note: The value of a constant must be assigned when you declare it.

content.text: Here is an example of declaring a constant in Go:
content.html: Here is an example of declaring a constant in Go:

content.code_html:
package main
import ("fmt")

const PI = 3.14

func main() {
  fmt.Println(PI)
}

content.text: There are two types of constants:
Typed constants are declared with a defined type:
content.html: Typed constants are declared with a defined type:

content.code_html:
package main
import ("fmt")

const A int = 1

func main() {
  fmt.Println(A)
}

content.text: Untyped constants are declared without a type:
content.html: Untyped constants are declared without a type:

content.code_html:
package main
import ("fmt")

const A = 1

func main() {
  fmt.Println(A)
}

content.text: Note: In this case, the type of the constant is inferred from the value (means the compiler decides the type of the constant, based on the value).
content.html: Note: In this case, the type of the constant is inferred from the value (means the compiler decides the type of the constant, based on the value).

content.text: When a constant is declared, it is not possible to change the value later:
content.html: When a constant is declared, it is not possible to change the value later:

content.code_html:
package main
import ("fmt")

func main() {
  const A = 1
  A = 2
  fmt.Println(A)
}

content.text: Multiple constants can be grouped together into a block for readability:
content.html: Multiple constants can be grouped together into a block for readability:

content.code_html:
package main
import ("fmt")

const (
  A int = 1
  B = 3.14
  C = "Hi!"
)

func main() {
  fmt.Println(A)
  fmt.Println(B)
  fmt.Println(C)
}
